aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription:
Cash value is calculated based on interest rate (0.04) and number of guaranteed period in year.
Paid up amount = cash value divided by Nb years divided by 12.
aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWLIClaimRuleEngineWithCashValue) (Def Version:2) (Implem Version:1)
uses WFTypes, aWFRuleDesc
function Interestcalculation(Amount : Num8, Annuityduration : Int4, Interestrate : tWFPercent) return tWFNum8 uses aWFStandAloneRule
var tmpRule : aWFRuleDesc
tmpRule = self.GetExactRuleToExecuteFromRankInRuleDesc(0, self.CurrentDate) if tmpRule <> Nil aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(Amount, 0, tmpRule) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(Annuityduration, 1, tmpRule) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(Interestrate, 2, tmpRule) tmpRule.GetStandAloneResult(_Result, self) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).CleanParamsAfterExecution(tmpRule) else self.AppendComment('No rule version defined at this date') endIf endFunc
function Coverage__Dynamic_Data__Guaranteedperiodinyear return Int4 type tpValue : .Int4
var p : Int4
if self.EvaluateFieldDescFromRank(1, 5, 'Coverage__Dynamic_Data__Guaranteedperiodinyear') p = tpValue(self.pFieldValue). _Result = p endIf endFunc
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : Num8) Result = self.Interestcalculation(self.Option__PaidUpPremiumAmount, self.Coverage__Dynamic_Data__Guaranteedperiodinyear, 0.04) endProc
aWFRuleDesc.Name: Paid out Calculation

aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription: The indefinite annuity rate formula gives the annual rate conversion of the beneficiary capital based on age and initial interest rate.
aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWLIClaimRuleEngineWithCashValue) (Def Version:1) (Implem Version:1)
uses WFTypes, aWFRuleDesc
function IndefiniteAnnuityRate(Age : Int4, InterestRate : Int4) return tWFNum8 uses aWFStandAloneRule
var tmpRule : aWFRuleDesc
tmpRule = self.GetExactRuleToExecuteFromRankInRuleDesc(0, self.CurrentDate) if tmpRule <> Nil aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(Age, 0, tmpRule) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(InterestRate, 1, tmpRule) tmpRule.GetStandAloneResult(_Result, self) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).CleanParamsAfterExecution(tmpRule) else self.AppendComment('No rule version defined at this date') endIf endFunc
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : Num8) var AgeAtRetirement : Int4
AgeAtRetirement = self.NumberOfYearsBetweenTwoDates(self.Subscriber__BirthDate, self.Loss__EventDate) Result = self.Option__PaidUpPremiumAmount * self.IndefiniteAnnuityRate(AgeAtRetirement, 0) endProc

aWFStandAloneRule.Name: IndefiniteAnnuityRate

aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription: The survivor will keep getting annuities
aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWLIClaimRuleEngineWithCashValue) (Def Version:3) (Implem Version:1)
uses WFTypes, aWFRuleDesc
type tWF_Generated_Annuitypaymentphase_318769344_15 : (Joint, Survivor, Notapplicable)
function IndefiniteAnnuityRate(Age : Int4, InterestRate : Int4) return tWFNum8 uses aWFStandAloneRule
var tmpRule : aWFRuleDesc
tmpRule = self.GetExactRuleToExecuteFromRankInRuleDesc(0, self.CurrentDate) if tmpRule <> Nil aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(Age, 0, tmpRule) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(InterestRate, 1, tmpRule) tmpRule.GetStandAloneResult(_Result, self) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).CleanParamsAfterExecution(tmpRule) else self.AppendComment('No rule version defined at this date') endIf endFunc
function DeliveredService__Classifications__Annuitypaymentphase return tWF_Generated_Annuitypaymentphase_318769344_15 if self.EvaluateClassificationFromRank(1, 11, 'DeliveredService__Classifications__Annuitypaymentphase') _Result = tWF_Generated_Annuitypaymentphase_318769344_15(self.V_ForClassificationEvaluation) endIf endFunc
function Coverage__Dynamic_Data__Whenjointly_Lifereducedby_ return tWFPercent type tpValue : .tWFPercent
var p : tWFPercent
if self.EvaluateFieldDescFromRank(2, 5, 'Coverage__Dynamic_Data__Whenjointly_Lifereducedby_') p = tpValue(self.pFieldValue). _Result = p endIf endFunc
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : Num8) var AgeAtRetirement : Int4
if self.DeliveredService__Classifications__Annuitypaymentphase = Joint AgeAtRetirement = self.NumberOfYearsBetweenTwoDates(self.Subscriber__BirthDate, self.Loss__EventDate) Result = self.Option__PaidUpPremiumAmount * self.IndefiniteAnnuityRate(AgeAtRetirement, 0) * 0.9 * (1.7 - self.Coverage__Dynamic_Data__Whenjointly_Lifereducedby_) else AgeAtRetirement = self.NumberOfYearsBetweenTwoDates(self.Subscriber__BirthDate, self.Loss__EventDate) Result = self.Option__PaidUpPremiumAmount * self.IndefiniteAnnuityRate(AgeAtRetirement, 0) * 0.9 * (1.7 - self.Coverage__Dynamic_Data__Whenjointly_Lifereducedby_) * self.Coverage__Dynamic_Data__Whenjointly_Lifereducedby_ endIf endProc

aWLICashValue_MixedProduct.Description: {\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss\fprq2\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}{\f1\fnil MS Sans Serif;}{\f2\fnil\fcharset2 Symbol;}} {\colortbl ;\red128\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;} \viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang2057\f0\fs16 This allows you to convert a lump sum of money into an \cf1\b annuity\b0 \cf0 so that you can immediately \par receive income. Payments generally start about a month after you purchase the annuity. This \par type of annuity offers financial security in the form of income payments for the rest of your life. \par In other words, you cannot outlive it.\par \par \cf1\b Immediate annuities\cf0 \b0 allow you to:\par \pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720 Supplement your current income. If you are nearing retirement, you may consider \line transferring another savings or investment account into an immediate annuity. You \line can also move the proceeds from a deferred annuity into an immediate annuity.\par {\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Pay taxes only on the portion of your immediate annuity payments that is considered \line earnings. You are not taxed on the portion that is principal. The principal is the initial \line deposit made with funds that have already been taxed.\par \pard\par Like deferred annuities, immediate annuities can be fixed or variable. Fixed immediate annuity \par income payments are pegged to the amount you contribute, your age and the interest rate at \par the time of purchase. Those payments to you will not go up or down. \cf1\b Variable immediate \par annuity\b0 \cf0 payments vary with the investments you chose.\cf2\lang1036\f1\par }
